    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Engineered for the purist, this 997-generation Carrera features the 3.6L flat-six M96/05 powerplant, delivering a linear torque curve and a distinctive boxer howl. The 6-speed manual transaxle offers short-throw precision, while the chassis benefits from Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) for adaptable damping and optimized roll stiffness. The braking system utilizes four-piston monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors, ensuring minimal thermal fade during spirited driving. While the exterior shows the honest patina of a driver-focused vehicle, the mechanical vitals are robust, featuring a recently serviced cooling system and verified cylinder wall integrity via borescope. This is a high-revving, rear-engine icon with communicative hydraulic steering and exceptional lateral grip, ready for the next apex.",
